article.description: Hicks leads CS Northridge over Montana State 72-65
article.headline: Hicks leads CS Northridge over Montana State 72-65
article.linkText: Hicks leads CS Northridge over Montana State 72-65
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Stephan Hicks scored 23 points and Stephen Maxwell added 15 to lead Cal State Northridge to a 72-65 victory over Montana State on Wednesday night. The Matadors had a 16-point lead with 5:27 remaining, but the Bobcats pulled within six, 66-60, with 19 seconds to play. The Matadors answered when Hicks made four free throws and Tre Hale-Edmerson scored to make it 72-63 with six seconds left. Marcus Colbert hit two free throws for the Bobcats with four seconds remaining to cap the scoring. Holm had 20 points and was 5 of 12 from beyond the arc. Colbert scored 15 points and Michael Dison 11 for Montana State (0-3), which shot just 22 of 64 for 34 percent from the floor. CS Northridge (1-2) got its first win after losing against nationally-ranked San Diego State and Arizona to open its season.
